            <abstract>
                <p>Magic prayer containing <foreign xml:lang="gez">ʾasmāt</foreign>. According to the Greek title, given in 
                    <ref type="mss" corresp="BAVet118"/>, the prayer is intended to provide love and happiness.
                    The use of this short text is explained in <ref type="mss" corresp="BAVet118"/>, fol. 77rb, in Greek and Gǝʿǝz-Amharic, as follows: 
                    <q xml:lang="grc">τά άνωθεν τά γράφης σε πετζή γενας μπράια μεγάλη</q>
                    <q xml:lang="am">የላይኛውን፡ ቃል፡ በብርሃና፡ ጸሀፎ፡ <surplus resp="PRS4805Grebaut PRS9530Tisseran">ለ</surplus>ትጽህፎ፡ በወርቅ፡ ቀለም፡ 
                        በሰባ<supplied reason="omitted">ዕ</supplied>ቱ፡ ቀለማት፡ ፪<del rend="expunctuated">ገ</del>ጊዜ፡</q>
                </p>
            </abstract>
